<paragraph blockId="22.[227,1437,1711,1808]" pageId="22" pageNumber="32">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Korn" authorityYear="2001" box="[227,337,1712,1737]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Taouzitidae" genus="Taouzites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ammonoidea" pageId="22" pageNumber="32" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[227,337,1712,1737]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="32">Taouzites</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
presents the morphological end member of an evolutionary series in the Givetian, which, starting from simple gephuroceratids, is characterised by a flattening of the conch with a sharpening venter and simultaneous proliferation of the umbilical lobes (
<bibRefCitation author="Korn D." box="[944,1076,1782,1808]" pageId="22" pageNumber="32" pagination="193 - 215" refId="ref18127" refString="Korn D. 2001. Morphometric evolution and phylogeny of Palaeozoic ammonoids. Early and Middle Devonian. Acta Geologica Polonica 51: 193 - 215." type="journal article" year="2001">Korn 2001</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
